# Railway builds this app with Nixpacks (see railway.toml). The repo's
# Dockerfile is the offline-selftest image (agent.py + SDK only, no web
# stack); on CLI uploads Railway's build detection preferred that Dockerfile
# over the config-as-code builder pin — observed live on the first deploy.
# Excluding it from uploads makes the Nixpacks pin unconditional.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# Local secrets and runtime data must never ride the upload archive
# (the CLI honors .gitignore, but a key should not depend on that).
.env
audit_log.jsonl
evals/corrections.json
HANDOFF-*.md
